1
00:00:05,040 --> 00:00:07,760
Si, are you ready to be my life partner?

2
00:00:07,800 --> 00:00:09,280
I'm ready

3
00:00:09,480 --> 00:00:12,600
to be your life partner forever.

4
00:00:12,760 --> 00:00:15,680
I already have a wife!

5
00:00:18,560 --> 00:00:20,600
P', who is that woman?

6
00:00:20,640 --> 00:00:22,560
Her name is Tookta.

7
00:00:22,600 --> 00:00:24,320
"Her name is Tookta."

8
00:00:24,320 --> 00:00:26,680
No matter how badly you act,

9
00:00:26,840 --> 00:00:28,760
I'll still love you the same.

10
00:00:29,080 --> 00:00:30,400
P'Klao.

11
00:00:30,440 --> 00:00:33,600
My mom said you raise buffaloes?

12
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:34,800
What's wrong with you?

13
00:00:34,840 --> 00:00:36,240
Why are you being so ridiculous?

14
00:00:36,240 --> 00:00:38,240
Is being jealous of my own girlfriend ridiculous?

15
00:00:44,760 --> 00:00:45,800
Song, sweetheart.

16
00:00:46,760 --> 00:00:49,120
My eyes aren’t playing tricks on me, right?

17
00:00:50,240 --> 00:00:52,600
I’m seeing the exact same thing you are.

18
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:55,880
Our house suddenly has buffaloes

19
00:00:56,720 --> 00:00:58,160
chickens

20
00:01:00,440 --> 00:01:01,720
and

21
00:01:02,560 --> 00:01:03,600
a cat.

22
00:01:08,720 --> 00:01:10,920
Since when did our house become a zoo?

23
00:01:10,920 --> 00:01:12,760
What is going on here?

24
00:01:13,440 --> 00:01:15,360
Oh, you’re back?

25
00:01:15,360 --> 00:01:17,320
Mom, Dad, Song.

26
00:01:18,520 --> 00:01:19,640
So?

27
00:01:19,960 --> 00:01:21,039
Do you like them?

28
00:01:21,080 --> 00:01:22,880
They’re my pets.

29
00:01:23,280 --> 00:01:25,080
Your pets?

30
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:28,960
Aren’t these the animals we saw at Klao’s house?

31
00:01:29,960 --> 00:01:32,600
Uh, then what are they doing here?

32
00:01:40,120 --> 00:01:42,840
Si, what are you doing?

33
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:48,320
Si.

34
00:01:48,759 --> 00:01:50,560
Where are you taking the kids?

35
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:54,640
Even though you raised Pidpee,
Muedmon, Jon, and Pao

36
00:01:54,680 --> 00:01:56,280
we’re married now.

37
00:01:56,320 --> 00:01:58,680
I’ll consider everything that belongs to you

38
00:01:58,720 --> 00:02:00,240
as mine too.

39
00:02:00,720 --> 00:02:02,600
I’m taking the kids home with me.

40
00:02:02,640 --> 00:02:04,160
Your house in Bangkok?

41
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:07,200
And how are you taking them there?

42
00:02:07,240 --> 00:02:09,160
Just like this. Why?

43
00:02:09,759 --> 00:02:10,960
Don’t try to stop me

44
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,440
because it’s not going to work.

45
00:02:13,360 --> 00:02:14,400
Si.

46
00:02:14,520 --> 00:02:16,360
You’re still acting like this.

47
00:02:16,480 --> 00:02:18,240
because you’re still mad at me, right?

48
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:19,520
You don’t need to ask me.

49
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:21,160
You know exactly what you did.

50
00:02:21,880 --> 00:02:22,880
Si.

51
00:02:22,920 --> 00:02:25,160
You’re still not over being mad at me?

52
00:02:25,560 --> 00:02:27,000
It’s such a small thing.

53
00:02:27,040 --> 00:02:28,920
How many times do I have to say

54
00:02:28,920 --> 00:02:31,160
that Tookta and I are nothing.

55
00:02:31,160 --> 00:02:32,680
We’ve just known each other a long time.

56
00:02:32,720 --> 00:02:35,320
so we just greet each other normally, that’s all.

57
00:02:35,560 --> 00:02:37,760
It may be a small thing to you.

58
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:39,320
but it’s a big deal to me.

59
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:40,360
Do you understand?

60
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:42,920
And how are you taking them there?

61
00:02:42,920 --> 00:02:44,840
Can you even take care of them?

62
00:02:45,320 --> 00:02:46,880
Why wouldn’t I be able to?

63
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:49,040
Pidpee and Muedmon are super easy to raise.

64
00:02:49,040 --> 00:02:50,720
As long as they have water and grass

65
00:02:50,760 --> 00:02:52,040
they’ll be fine.

66
00:02:52,079 --> 00:02:53,840
As for Jon, he can live anywhere.

67
00:02:53,880 --> 00:02:55,200
They just need a wide space.

68
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:57,680
And my house is even bigger than this one.

69
00:02:58,280 --> 00:03:00,800
As for Pao, he’s even more attached to me than to you.

70
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:03,840
He might want to stay with me more than with you.

71
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:06,160
But they’re not used to Bangkok’s weather.

72
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:09,120
I’m worried and scared something
might happen to them.

73
00:03:09,160 --> 00:03:12,000
There are plenty of good vets in Bangkok.

74
00:03:12,040 --> 00:03:14,200
I’m not going to let them get sick and die.

75
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:17,040
And did you ask your mom
and dad for permission yet?

76
00:03:17,079 --> 00:03:19,520
Your house is huge and luxurious.

77
00:03:19,520 --> 00:03:20,760
Your parents might not want...

78
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:22,440
Why do I need permission?

79
00:03:22,480 --> 00:03:23,880
That’s my house too.

80
00:03:23,880 --> 00:03:25,440
I can do whatever I want.

81
00:03:26,240 --> 00:03:27,840
Are you done talking yet?

82
00:03:27,960 --> 00:03:29,120
So I can leave.

83
00:03:29,320 --> 00:03:30,560
Si.

84
00:03:31,120 --> 00:03:32,720
Please don’t go.

85
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:34,840
You, from now on

86
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:36,960
don’t let me see your face again.

87
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:40,040
I don’t care if you live or die.

88
00:03:40,079 --> 00:03:41,440
And don’t contact me anymore.

89
00:03:41,440 --> 00:03:43,320
I don’t want to see your face again.

90
00:03:47,200 --> 00:03:48,640
Go, hurry up.

91
00:03:56,200 --> 00:03:57,200
Si.

92
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:59,920
You can’t be this selfish.

93
00:04:00,120 --> 00:04:02,120
You two just got married.

94
00:04:02,160 --> 00:04:03,920
And you’re already fighting?

95
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:05,520
Exactly, sweetheart.

96
00:04:05,720 --> 00:04:07,320
Why can’t you two just talk things out?

97
00:04:07,320 --> 00:04:10,360
Instead of getting mad
and moving everything out like this.

98
00:04:10,640 --> 00:04:12,320
Are you two really going to make it?

99
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:13,760
Can’t help it.

100
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:15,680
She was flirting with another woman.

101
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:18,079
People who do something wrong deserve this.

102
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:21,320
But these little guys didn’t do anything wrong.

103
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:23,920
Dragging them around like this
might make them sick.

104
00:04:23,960 --> 00:04:25,960
And besides

105
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:28,120
your father is allergic to cat fur.

106
00:04:30,360 --> 00:04:31,920
Did you forget already?

107
00:04:31,960 --> 00:04:34,400
I didn’t forget.
I sneeze that loud every day.

108
00:04:36,080 --> 00:04:37,159
Don’t worry.

109
00:04:37,159 --> 00:04:39,960
I already planned everything out
Pao’s going to sleep in my room.

110
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:43,560
He won’t wander around
and bother Mom and Dad for sure.

111
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:46,800
As for Pidpee, Muedmon, and Jon

112
00:04:47,080 --> 00:04:49,040
they can stay in our garden.

113
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:50,680
Our garden is huge and spacious.

114
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:53,360
The kids will definitely be comfortable there, right?

115
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:54,440
Pidpee.

116
00:04:55,320 --> 00:04:56,440
As for P’Klao

117
00:04:56,440 --> 00:04:57,920
I really want to know too

118
00:04:57,960 --> 00:04:59,560
how long she can live alone

119
00:04:59,560 --> 00:05:01,520
without Pidpee and Muedmon

120
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:03,560
without me, Jon, and Pao.

121
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:04,960
How many days can she last alone?

122
00:05:06,040 --> 00:05:08,120
Can you handle it?

123
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,240
Are you okay, Dad?

124
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:11,000
What are you doing?

125
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:12,840
I’m home alone

126
00:07:12,840 --> 00:07:15,000
without you and the kids.

127
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:16,360
I’m so lonely.

128
00:07:33,480 --> 00:07:36,800
P’Klao.

129
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:42,680
Pew pew.

130
00:07:45,320 --> 00:07:47,400
Pew pew.

131
00:07:47,440 --> 00:07:48,560
Tookta.

132
00:07:48,880 --> 00:07:50,400
How did you get in here?

133
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:53,720
Well, you left the door wide open for me

134
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:55,560
so I came in.

135
00:07:57,120 --> 00:07:58,400
Hey, hey, hey.

136
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:02,600
Ta-da.

137
00:08:02,640 --> 00:08:05,520
Sour curry.

138
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:10,320
Son-in-law eggs.

139
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:13,200
Looks like my mom’s definitely getting you

140
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:15,920
as a son-in-law for sure.

141
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:18,120
Have you eaten yet?

142
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:19,880
I already ate.

143
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:21,800
Thank you so much.

144
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:24,400
- You're welcome.
- I'll go put these

145
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:28,120
into bowls and save them for tomorrow.

146
00:08:28,120 --> 00:08:29,880
Wait here for a sec.

147
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:32,080
Sure.

148
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:33,440
Just a sec.

149
00:08:40,039 --> 00:08:42,559
Moral support.

150
00:08:43,080 --> 00:08:46,240
- In case you get tired.
- Moral support.

151
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:49,440
Be careful walking.

152
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:05,040
Brother-in-law.

153
00:09:05,760 --> 00:09:07,240
Sister-in-law.

154
00:09:07,280 --> 00:09:08,920
Sister-in-law.

155
00:09:09,040 --> 00:09:10,600
And this is

156
00:09:10,640 --> 00:09:13,440
my sister-in-law.

157
00:09:22,760 --> 00:09:23,800
Done.

158
00:09:24,720 --> 00:09:25,920
So,

159
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,840
are you home alone?

160
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:30,560
Oh.

161
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:33,040
Si is working upstairs.

162
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:37,040
Really? But this morning,
I saw your girlfriend drive out.

163
00:09:37,080 --> 00:09:38,320
She still hasn't come back yet.

164
00:09:38,360 --> 00:09:40,360
Did you two have a fight or something?

165
00:09:47,760 --> 00:09:48,880
Tookta.

166
00:09:49,040 --> 00:09:50,720
I'm sorry.

167
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:52,680
But I need to be honest with you.

168
00:09:52,680 --> 00:09:56,080
I'm already married.

169
00:09:56,400 --> 00:10:00,280
And I've always seen you as my little sister.

170
00:10:00,520 --> 00:10:03,400
But if you come into my house right now,

171
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:05,720
and someone happens to see us,

172
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:07,400
they might get the wrong idea.

173
00:10:07,400 --> 00:10:09,680
I think you should head home first.

174
00:10:10,400 --> 00:10:14,320
And besides, I've been really busy lately.

175
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:16,280
We probably won't get to talk much.

176
00:10:16,280 --> 00:10:17,760
You understand, right?

177
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:21,560
Aha, your girlfriend

178
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:23,520
must be jealous of me, huh?

179
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:24,920
But that can't be helped.

180
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:27,680
I'm just too pretty.

181
00:10:31,040 --> 00:10:33,160
If you're uncomfortable today,

182
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:35,160
then I'll head back for now.

183
00:10:35,160 --> 00:10:38,360
I'll come see you another day instead.

184
00:10:40,480 --> 00:10:44,280
Actually, next time if you want
to bring me something,

185
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:46,680
you can just ask your mom to bring it over.

186
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:48,600
Or just call me.

187
00:10:48,640 --> 00:10:50,160
I'll have someone pick it up.

188
00:10:50,560 --> 00:10:52,400
I'm scared

189
00:10:52,680 --> 00:10:54,360
my girlfriend might misunderstand.

190
00:10:58,200 --> 00:11:01,000
If you're that scared of your wife, then fine.

191
00:11:02,880 --> 00:11:04,560
I won't bring you anything again.

192
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:12,360
Give it back to me.

193
00:11:24,280 --> 00:11:26,200
I've done all this for you,

194
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:27,440
and if you still won't stop sulking,

195
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:28,840
I'm gonna get mad too.

196
00:11:29,240 --> 00:11:30,360
And look at this.

197
00:11:30,360 --> 00:11:31,800
You took all the kids with you.

198
00:11:31,960 --> 00:11:33,680
What am I supposed to do now?

199
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:37,320
Pao.

200
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:40,680
Why hasn't P'Klao come to make up with me yet?

201
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:42,440
Seriously,

202
00:11:42,480 --> 00:11:45,040
she hasn't even sent me a single text.

203
00:11:45,560 --> 00:11:48,160
Doesn't she miss me and you at all?

204
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:52,840
Just wait.

205
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:55,240
I'm gonna sulk even harder.

206
00:11:55,280 --> 00:11:56,280
You'll see.

207
00:11:56,640 --> 00:11:57,640
Right?

208
00:12:21,640 --> 00:12:22,640
I'm sulking here.

209
00:12:22,760 --> 00:12:23,960
Even with you here,

210
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:25,760
she still won't come make up with me.

211
00:12:34,360 --> 00:12:35,360
Hey.

212
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:36,680
I'm scared of chickens.

213
00:12:37,240 --> 00:12:38,520
Can you feed it for me?

214
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:40,240
You do it yourself.

215
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:42,840
Why are you scared of such a tiny chicken?

216
00:12:42,880 --> 00:12:46,440
- If you're not scared, then you do it.
- Just go feed it.

217
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:48,440
- You do it.
- No, you feed it.

218
00:12:50,320 --> 00:12:53,960
You said you weren't scared of chickens,
but look at your hands shaking.

219
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:55,480
My hands are not shaking.

220
00:12:55,480 --> 00:12:58,840
Then why'd you almost drop the tray?
Look, it's all spilled now.

221
00:12:59,720 --> 00:13:02,120
Here. Ow, look at this.

222
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:04,760
- The rice fell everywhere.
- Hey.

223
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:06,600
- Hey.
- What?

224
00:13:08,040 --> 00:13:10,560
- Chicken.
- Chicken? I know it's a chicken.

225
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:17,840
Chicken, chicken, chicken.

226
00:13:18,640 --> 00:13:20,800
Chicken, chicken, hey.

227
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:22,160
Hey.

228
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:24,440
Hey.

229
00:13:38,480 --> 00:13:39,480
Mom.

230
00:13:49,920 --> 00:13:51,320
What happened?

231
00:13:51,560 --> 00:13:52,760
No, no, no.

232
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:53,800
Take it over there.

233
00:13:53,800 --> 00:13:54,960
Take it over there.

234
00:13:54,960 --> 00:13:56,080
Take it away.

235
00:13:57,040 --> 00:13:58,040
Okay.

236
00:14:05,200 --> 00:14:06,440
What happened?

237
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:08,320
Why's it so chaotic, Mom?

238
00:14:08,560 --> 00:14:10,400
That chicken chased and pecked me.

239
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:12,480
Look, my hair's a total mess now.

240
00:14:12,840 --> 00:14:15,600
Then let's go inside, Mom. Come on.

241
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:16,960
Hey.

242
00:14:17,920 --> 00:14:18,920
Hey.

243
00:14:22,040 --> 00:14:23,040
Hey.

244
00:14:23,480 --> 00:14:25,200
Help me get down first.

245
00:14:26,360 --> 00:14:27,800
- Hey.
- Dad.

246
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:31,000
- I'm up here.
- What are you doing up there?

247
00:14:31,040 --> 00:14:32,360
Klao, dear.

248
00:14:32,360 --> 00:14:34,800
Can you help me get down?

249
00:14:35,320 --> 00:14:39,040
Uh... has the chicken gone away yet?

250
00:14:39,040 --> 00:14:40,920
- Yeah, it's gone.
- It's gone?

251
00:14:40,960 --> 00:14:42,360
Then I'm coming down now.

252
00:14:42,360 --> 00:14:44,400
How are you even getting down from there?

253
00:14:44,560 --> 00:14:46,040
Careful coming down, Dad.

254
00:14:57,040 --> 00:14:58,280
Hey.

255
00:15:01,960 --> 00:15:04,840
Ow, be gentle.

256
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:06,720
Seriously.

257
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:10,200
Acting all tough like you're not scared of chickens,

258
00:15:11,560 --> 00:15:13,480
but then you ran up a tree.

259
00:15:13,560 --> 00:15:14,680
Klao, look at him.

260
00:15:14,680 --> 00:15:18,560
- Acting reckless at his age.
- Oh please, you're one to talk.

261
00:15:18,560 --> 00:15:21,800
Look at your head.
Your hairpiece almost came off.

262
00:15:21,840 --> 00:15:23,120
No, it didn't.

263
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:24,560
Good thing Klao's here.

264
00:15:24,560 --> 00:15:26,600
Can you take your little minion back with you?

265
00:15:27,240 --> 00:15:30,320
Why did Si let you two

266
00:15:30,360 --> 00:15:32,440
feed Jon in the first place?

267
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:36,040
She didn't ask me to do it.

268
00:15:36,040 --> 00:15:38,600
But this morning, I saw her

269
00:15:38,880 --> 00:15:41,480
leave early, and she didn't look too happy.

270
00:15:41,520 --> 00:15:43,280
I got worried about the
buffaloes and the chicken.

271
00:15:43,280 --> 00:15:44,800
I was scared they wouldn't
have anything to eat.

272
00:15:44,800 --> 00:15:46,280
So I brought them some food.

273
00:15:46,280 --> 00:15:49,080
Then it jumped at me.
You saw what happened after that.

274
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:52,040
Please, can you just

275
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:54,400
take them back home?

276
00:15:55,160 --> 00:15:56,240
Take them back?

277
00:15:56,280 --> 00:15:58,360
I definitely will, but...

278
00:15:58,400 --> 00:15:59,560
Come on.

279
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:02,400
You don't have to give in to Si that much.

280
00:16:02,480 --> 00:16:06,120
She brought your little minions here,
so she should take some responsibility too.

281
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:10,240
Thank you, Mom and Dad, for understanding me.

282
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:13,720
Then let me leave them here
for a few more days, okay?

283
00:16:13,760 --> 00:16:15,040
A few days?

284
00:16:18,440 --> 00:16:20,240
But don't worry.

285
00:16:20,680 --> 00:16:23,720
I'll stop by and check on them every day.

286
00:16:23,720 --> 00:16:27,680
But please don't tell Si
that I came here.

287
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:32,800
Alright then, Klao.

288
00:16:32,840 --> 00:16:34,600
I'll help you out.

289
00:16:34,640 --> 00:16:37,360
Si needs to learn a lesson from this.

290
00:16:43,960 --> 00:16:45,040
For bruising.

291
00:16:45,080 --> 00:16:47,000
You should heal those bruises a bit.

292
00:16:52,920 --> 00:16:54,000
Are you guys hot?

293
00:16:54,240 --> 00:16:56,000
Wanna go swim out back?

294
00:16:56,040 --> 00:16:59,440
Or should we go sleep in the house with the AC on?

295
00:16:59,680 --> 00:17:00,680
Hey.

296
00:17:01,080 --> 00:17:02,240
Jon's so loud.

297
00:17:02,240 --> 00:17:03,680
Do you miss your big sis or what?

298
00:17:05,680 --> 00:17:06,960
P'Klao is so annoying!

299
00:17:07,319 --> 00:17:09,480
When is she gonna realize
she's making this hard for me?

300
00:17:10,480 --> 00:17:11,480
Here.

301
00:17:13,640 --> 00:17:16,960
Wow, does Si really have to go this far?

302
00:17:17,280 --> 00:17:19,000
I feel bad for her.

303
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:21,160
What should I do?

304
00:17:21,319 --> 00:17:23,119
You have to stay strong.

305
00:17:23,240 --> 00:17:25,680
Don't soften up yet.
Just hang in there.

306
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:29,000
I can't take it anymore.

307
00:17:29,040 --> 00:17:30,160
I'm lonely.

308
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:31,640
I miss Si.

309
00:17:31,680 --> 00:17:34,760
And I miss those little kids like crazy too.

310
00:17:35,240 --> 00:17:36,960
Stay strong. Hang in there.

311
00:17:39,560 --> 00:17:41,200
When is she gonna come make up with me?

312
00:17:41,240 --> 00:17:43,280
It's been days already.

313
00:17:44,320 --> 00:17:45,880
Right, Pidpee?

314
00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:50,560
Did all the maids take leave together?

315
00:17:50,600 --> 00:17:52,360
Then who's gonna clean up the buffalo poop?

316
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:53,720
Exactly.

317
00:17:53,760 --> 00:17:55,600
Last time you made the maids clean it up,

318
00:17:55,600 --> 00:17:58,480
so this time they all took leave together.

319
00:17:58,840 --> 00:18:00,000
How about this?

320
00:18:00,240 --> 00:18:01,840
You brought them here,

321
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:04,160
- so you deal with them yourself.
- No way.

322
00:18:04,160 --> 00:18:07,360
Mom, help me out here.

323
00:18:07,400 --> 00:18:08,400
Please?

324
00:18:09,080 --> 00:18:11,680
Wait, wait, wait. Hold on.

325
00:18:11,880 --> 00:18:12,880
Si.

326
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:15,040
You're the one who brought them here.

327
00:18:15,360 --> 00:18:17,920
I'm seriously scared of buffaloes.

328
00:18:17,960 --> 00:18:21,480
Last time the chicken chased me,
I nearly ran for my life.

329
00:18:21,480 --> 00:18:23,960
Your dad here almost went extinct.

330
00:18:25,160 --> 00:18:27,000
Alright then, take care of yourself.

331
00:18:27,040 --> 00:18:28,080
I'm leaving.

332
00:18:28,080 --> 00:18:30,000
- Let's go.
- Mom, Dad.

333
00:18:30,480 --> 00:18:32,280
Mom, Dad.

334
00:18:45,600 --> 00:18:47,040
Pidpee, Muedmon.

335
00:18:47,040 --> 00:18:50,560
What the heck did you two eat?
Why is there so much poop?

336
00:19:04,840 --> 00:19:06,440
That stupid P'Klao.

337
00:19:10,320 --> 00:19:12,680
That stupid P'Klao.

338
00:19:13,800 --> 00:19:15,400
Hey, that stupid P'Klao.

339
00:19:16,080 --> 00:19:18,200
When is she gonna come make up with me, huh?
Your big sis, I mean.

340
00:19:24,840 --> 00:19:26,120
That stupid P'Klao.

341
00:19:35,600 --> 00:19:37,400
That stupid P'Klao.

342
00:19:38,480 --> 00:19:39,960
Ugh, it stinks.

343
00:19:41,280 --> 00:19:43,800
I've washed it like ten times already.
Why does the smell still won't go away?

344
00:19:45,920 --> 00:19:47,120
Did the ring fall off?

345
00:19:55,760 --> 00:19:56,760
Just wait.

346
00:19:56,920 --> 00:19:59,200
I'm gonna make her suffer
when she comes to apologize.

347
00:20:19,440 --> 00:20:20,680
Pao.

348
00:20:22,080 --> 00:20:23,960
What the heck are you doing?

349
00:20:23,960 --> 00:20:26,000
Why did you trash my whole room?

350
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:29,800
You always cause trouble every...

351
00:20:33,280 --> 00:20:34,360
There's trash everywhere.

352
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:36,520
Why'd you do this?
Why are you so naughty?

353
00:20:36,560 --> 00:20:38,320
You're so stubborn.

354
00:20:38,840 --> 00:20:40,800
This is all because of your big sis.

355
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:42,680
She made everything such a mess.

356
00:20:42,720 --> 00:20:44,280
Just wait. If I see her,

357
00:20:44,320 --> 00:20:47,360
I'm gonna squeeze her to death.
Just wait.

358
00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:49,600
Help me clean up too.

359
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:52,600
Pao.

360
00:20:59,240 --> 00:21:00,280
Jae Puang.

361
00:21:02,440 --> 00:21:03,800
What's up, Jae Puang?

362
00:21:03,920 --> 00:21:05,680
P'Klao told you to call me, right?

363
00:21:05,960 --> 00:21:08,160
Then why doesn't she call me herself?

364
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:09,760
No, Si.

365
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:13,240
It's just... Klao, she...

366
00:21:13,280 --> 00:21:14,680
What about her?

367
00:21:14,680 --> 00:21:16,480
- Si.
- What happened to her?

368
00:21:16,520 --> 00:21:18,440
You need to stay calm, okay?

369
00:21:18,880 --> 00:21:20,840
It's just... she...

370
00:21:20,880 --> 00:21:22,600
She...

371
00:21:26,720 --> 00:21:28,440
Don't go.

372
00:21:28,480 --> 00:21:30,280
Whatever happens to you,
just go then.

373
00:21:30,320 --> 00:21:31,680
And don't ever contact me again.

374
00:21:31,720 --> 00:21:33,600
I don't want to see your face anymore.

375
00:22:22,200 --> 00:22:23,200
P'Klao.

376
00:22:23,440 --> 00:22:24,480
P'Klao.

377
00:22:25,960 --> 00:22:27,160
P'Klao.

378
00:22:27,840 --> 00:22:29,040
P'Klao.

379
00:22:30,440 --> 00:22:32,720
How could you leave me like this?

380
00:22:32,720 --> 00:22:35,000
Hey, I'm sorry.

381
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:37,200
Wake up, please.

382
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:39,120
Why did you leave me like this?

383
00:22:39,160 --> 00:22:42,560
You said we'd stay together forever.

384
00:22:43,840 --> 00:22:46,080
- Ma'am, ma'am.
- Why didn't you save her?

385
00:22:46,120 --> 00:22:48,320
- Ma'am.
- Why did you let her die?

386
00:22:48,680 --> 00:22:50,960
- Well...
- How could you be so cruel?

387
00:22:50,960 --> 00:22:52,160
Please, I...

388
00:22:52,320 --> 00:22:53,760
I'm begging you.

389
00:22:53,800 --> 00:22:56,440
- Can you bring her back somehow? Please.
- Ma'am, it's just...

390
00:22:56,440 --> 00:22:59,800
- I'll pay anything, just please...
- Well...

391
00:23:00,040 --> 00:23:03,800
- Ma'am, actually...
- Bring her back to life.

392
00:23:04,040 --> 00:23:05,440
Si.

393
00:23:09,840 --> 00:23:10,960
P'Klao.

394
00:23:15,920 --> 00:23:17,760
Is this your ghost?

395
00:23:21,880 --> 00:23:24,080
Did you come to say goodbye to me?

396
00:23:24,560 --> 00:23:25,880
I don't want this.

397
00:23:27,080 --> 00:23:28,200
P'Klao.

398
00:23:28,640 --> 00:23:31,320
I'm sorry, okay?

399
00:23:31,360 --> 00:23:34,960
Wake up, please.
I'm sorry.

400
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:47,640
Si.

401
00:23:50,360 --> 00:23:52,400
You're not dead?

402
00:23:58,240 --> 00:23:59,880
And who told you

403
00:23:59,880 --> 00:24:01,000
I was dead?

404
00:24:02,760 --> 00:24:04,080
Jae Puang.

405
00:24:04,080 --> 00:24:05,600
She called and told me

406
00:24:05,640 --> 00:24:07,360
you got hit by a car.

407
00:24:08,200 --> 00:24:10,240
Hey, I'm sorry.

408
00:24:10,240 --> 00:24:11,400
I thought

409
00:24:11,560 --> 00:24:15,080
- you were mad and left me already.
- Aww.

410
00:24:15,880 --> 00:24:17,920
I think Jae misunderstood.

411
00:24:18,040 --> 00:24:20,280
I just helped someone
who got hit by a car.

412
00:24:20,560 --> 00:24:22,440
Then I took them to the hospital.

413
00:24:22,760 --> 00:24:24,080
I'm not dead.

414
00:24:24,760 --> 00:24:25,880
Really?

415
00:24:25,880 --> 00:24:27,760
Yeah. Here, touch me.

416
00:24:39,440 --> 00:24:40,840
No more crying, okay?

417
00:24:41,160 --> 00:24:43,920
- That's my brave girl.
- You scared me to death.

418
00:24:51,680 --> 00:24:53,720
You don't have to cry anymore.

419
00:24:54,040 --> 00:24:56,160
I'm not dead after all.

420
00:25:29,320 --> 00:25:31,040
Let's go home, okay?

421
00:25:31,320 --> 00:25:32,440
Okay.

422
00:25:32,720 --> 00:25:33,720
So,

423
00:25:33,800 --> 00:25:35,920
are you still mad at me?

424
00:25:37,480 --> 00:25:38,640
I'm not mad anymore.

425
00:25:39,040 --> 00:25:41,080
I won't be mad at you ever again.

426
00:25:42,120 --> 00:25:43,600
After what happened,

427
00:25:43,760 --> 00:25:46,880
it made me realize I can't live without you.

428
00:25:47,480 --> 00:25:49,640
And I won't stay away from you again,

429
00:25:49,640 --> 00:25:51,080
not even for a single day.

430
00:25:52,360 --> 00:25:53,840
If back then,

431
00:25:54,360 --> 00:25:56,200
something had really happened to you,

432
00:25:57,080 --> 00:26:00,280
I would've regretted leaving you
for the rest of my life.

433
00:26:00,600 --> 00:26:03,800
I won't stay away from you either.

434
00:26:04,160 --> 00:26:06,160
We're gonna stay together forever.

435
00:26:06,880 --> 00:26:08,360
Do you know

436
00:26:08,560 --> 00:26:11,360
how much I missed you?

437
00:26:12,520 --> 00:26:15,000
We should thank Jae Puang
for misunderstanding things.

438
00:26:15,040 --> 00:26:17,000
That's what got us back together.

439
00:26:18,480 --> 00:26:21,880
Then I should give her a huge reward.

440
00:26:22,200 --> 00:26:23,440
Then let's go home.

441
00:26:23,600 --> 00:26:24,720
Hold on.

442
00:26:25,600 --> 00:26:27,800
We're definitely going home, but...

443
00:26:27,960 --> 00:26:29,280
But...

444
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:31,000
But...

445
00:26:32,920 --> 00:26:35,720
I have a reward for you too.

446
00:26:36,360 --> 00:26:38,840
Pidpee, Muedmon,
wait for us for a bit, okay?

447
00:26:38,880 --> 00:26:40,280
Come on.

448
00:28:01,560 --> 00:28:03,160
You know,

449
00:28:04,960 --> 00:28:06,800
ever since you left,

450
00:28:08,200 --> 00:28:10,200
the house has been so quiet.

451
00:28:12,000 --> 00:28:14,360
And with the kids gone too,

452
00:28:15,400 --> 00:28:16,800
it felt even quieter.

453
00:28:18,600 --> 00:28:20,400
It made me wonder

454
00:28:21,440 --> 00:28:22,800
how I even managed

455
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:26,280
to live alone before this.

456
00:28:29,960 --> 00:28:31,760
A life without you,

457
00:28:33,040 --> 00:28:34,760
without the kids,

458
00:28:36,360 --> 00:28:38,200
really feels empty.

459
00:28:41,000 --> 00:28:42,680
My life

460
00:28:43,160 --> 00:28:44,600
without you

461
00:28:45,800 --> 00:28:47,480
feels empty too.

462
00:29:10,000 --> 00:29:11,200
Klao.

463
00:29:12,160 --> 00:29:13,880
Klao. Oh.

464
00:29:13,880 --> 00:29:16,560
- Hello, Village Headman.
- Uh, hello.

465
00:29:16,600 --> 00:29:18,000
Hello, Village Headman.

466
00:29:18,040 --> 00:29:19,200
Hello.

467
00:29:19,280 --> 00:29:20,280
Klao,

468
00:29:20,440 --> 00:29:21,720
I heard

469
00:29:22,080 --> 00:29:24,800
you went to look at land in Nonthaburi.

470
00:29:25,680 --> 00:29:27,480
Are you buying more land or

471
00:29:27,800 --> 00:29:29,240
moving there?

472
00:29:31,040 --> 00:29:32,440
Is something wrong?

473
00:29:32,680 --> 00:29:34,720
Why are you suddenly moving?

474
00:29:35,360 --> 00:29:36,360
Hm?

475
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:39,000
Huh?

476
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:41,520
Something this serious happened,

477
00:29:41,600 --> 00:29:43,600
so why didn't you tell me?

478
00:29:43,800 --> 00:29:45,720
We're married now.

479
00:29:46,240 --> 00:29:48,880
Si, if you don't listen to me,

480
00:29:48,920 --> 00:29:51,640
then you won't hear what I have to say.

481
00:29:55,720 --> 00:29:56,920
Alright.

482
00:29:57,040 --> 00:30:00,440
Then tell me everything.

483
00:30:01,600 --> 00:30:02,840
Yeah.

484
00:30:02,920 --> 00:30:04,880
I really did go look at the land.

485
00:30:05,160 --> 00:30:08,720
Ever since the day you got mad at me
and went back to Bangkok,

486
00:30:09,240 --> 00:30:10,720
I've been overthinking everything.

487
00:30:11,040 --> 00:30:14,000
I didn't know how to make you believe

488
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:16,120
that Tookta and I had nothing going on.

489
00:30:16,720 --> 00:30:20,200
So I thought I'd move us somewhere else
and get it over with.

490
00:30:20,800 --> 00:30:22,560
So you'd feel at ease.

491
00:30:22,840 --> 00:30:24,720
Hey...

492
00:30:25,240 --> 00:30:27,800
You went through all this because of me?

493
00:30:29,000 --> 00:30:30,840
I'm sorry.

494
00:30:30,880 --> 00:30:33,440
I made things so difficult for you.

495
00:30:37,120 --> 00:30:39,160
You don't have to apologize to me.

496
00:30:39,720 --> 00:30:41,720
I'd do anything for you.

497
00:30:42,400 --> 00:30:43,480
I'd even give you

498
00:30:43,680 --> 00:30:45,280
my whole life.

499
00:30:46,360 --> 00:30:47,680
But just promise me

500
00:30:48,080 --> 00:30:50,160
you won't run away again.

501
00:30:53,880 --> 00:30:55,720
I'm sorry.

502
00:31:05,440 --> 00:31:06,440
Si,

503
00:31:07,640 --> 00:31:10,240
but do you know something?

504
00:31:11,240 --> 00:31:12,760
Trust

505
00:31:13,400 --> 00:31:15,600
isn't something I can build for you.

506
00:31:16,720 --> 00:31:19,520
You have to build it yourself.

507
00:31:20,360 --> 00:31:24,320
Because no matter how loyal I am
or how much I love you,

508
00:31:25,520 --> 00:31:28,600
if you still doubt me
and can't trust me,

509
00:31:29,520 --> 00:31:31,680
everything will fall apart anyway.

510
00:31:37,560 --> 00:31:38,680
Okay.

511
00:31:39,040 --> 00:31:40,640
I promise

512
00:31:40,680 --> 00:31:43,640
that I'll trust and believe in you.

513
00:31:46,040 --> 00:31:47,360
Thank you,

514
00:31:47,520 --> 00:31:48,960
my good girl.

515
00:31:49,960 --> 00:31:50,960
But...

516
00:31:52,040 --> 00:31:54,800
I'm really sorry too.

517
00:31:54,920 --> 00:31:57,320
I never realized

518
00:31:57,520 --> 00:31:59,520
how hard things were for you.

519
00:32:01,760 --> 00:32:03,120
It's okay.

520
00:32:03,440 --> 00:32:04,840
At least

521
00:32:04,880 --> 00:32:06,840
everything that happened

522
00:32:07,280 --> 00:32:08,800
made us realize

523
00:32:09,000 --> 00:32:11,320
how much we love each other.

524
00:32:11,880 --> 00:32:14,760
And from now on,
no matter what happens,

525
00:32:15,240 --> 00:32:17,440
we'll use our love

526
00:32:17,600 --> 00:32:19,720
to get through everything together.

527
00:32:44,840 --> 00:32:47,040
Eat up, you little tapeworm.

528
00:32:50,400 --> 00:32:52,000
Sweet as hell.

529
00:32:53,360 --> 00:32:55,720
Mwah mwah mwah.

530
00:32:56,800 --> 00:32:58,120
Ew.

531
00:33:34,960 --> 00:33:36,560
If you talk to another woman,

532
00:33:36,600 --> 00:33:39,560
I won't just take Pidpee, Muedmon,
Pao, and Jon home.

533
00:33:39,560 --> 00:33:40,960
I'll take your whole house...

534
00:33:58,240 --> 00:34:02,080
- Si, look at this.
- What is it?

535
00:34:02,120 --> 00:34:05,120
I got an award last night.

536
00:34:05,160 --> 00:34:07,800
And Pooh and Pavel were there in person too.

537
00:34:08,320 --> 00:34:10,280
They're so handsome in real life.

538
00:34:11,199 --> 00:34:13,760
- Here, look.
- They really are. Let me see.

539
00:34:13,800 --> 00:34:14,800
Here.

540
00:34:16,080 --> 00:34:18,960
Whoa, Entertainer of the Year?

541
00:34:19,320 --> 00:34:21,639
- That's such a fancy award name.
- Yeah, right?

542
00:34:23,080 --> 00:34:25,239
You're really amazing.

543
00:34:26,120 --> 00:34:27,679
Amazing my ass.

544
00:34:27,800 --> 00:34:30,120
I should be thanking you instead

545
00:34:30,159 --> 00:34:31,840
for teaching me how to make content.

546
00:34:32,960 --> 00:34:34,520
Ever since you moved here,

547
00:34:34,520 --> 00:34:36,679
you've only brought good things into our lives.

548
00:34:36,719 --> 00:34:38,120
Thank you so much.

549
00:34:39,159 --> 00:34:43,000
You're exaggerating.
I'm not that amazing.

550
00:34:43,840 --> 00:34:45,320
Look at her acting humble.

551
00:34:45,360 --> 00:34:46,719
Are you an imposter or something?

552
00:34:46,719 --> 00:34:49,239
- Take off your mask.
- Hey.

553
00:34:50,639 --> 00:34:52,120
But honestly,

554
00:34:52,239 --> 00:34:53,719
I really am pretty amazing though, right?

555
00:34:53,760 --> 00:34:56,120
Ah, now the mask is off.
This is the real me.

556
00:34:56,159 --> 00:34:57,480
Hey.

557
00:34:57,760 --> 00:34:58,840
Just kidding.

558
00:34:59,280 --> 00:35:00,360
Anyway,

559
00:35:00,400 --> 00:35:02,640
